about.summary: give dtool ability to create dataset where data directory is a symlink.

name: dtool_symlink
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set name = "dtool_symlink" %}
{% set reponame = "dtool-symlink" %}
{% set author = "jic-dtool" %}
{% set version = "0.3.0" %}
{% set sha256 = "355d7b3138dc1675c682632107875c49c112922d43f6b200900217d1f9a43559" %}

package:
  name: {{ name|lower }}
  version: {{ version }}

source:
  url: https://github.com/{{ author }}/{{ reponame }}/archive/{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: {{ sha256 }}

build:
  number: 0
  noarch: python
  preserve_egg_dir: True
  script: "{{ PYTHON }} -m pip install . --no-deps -vv"

requirements:
  host:
    - python
    - pip
  run:
    - python
    - click
    - setuptools
    - dtoolcore
    - dtool_cli

test:
  imports:
    - dtool_symlink
    - dtool_symlink.storagebroker

about:
  home: http://github.com/{{ author }}/{{ reponame }}
  license: MIT
  license_file: LICENSE.rst
  summary: 'give dtool ability to create dataset where data directory is a symlink.'

  dev_url: https://github.com/{{ author }}/{{ reponame }}

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - pvanheus
